CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 13, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Musician and Fan - Bennie [Benny] Carter paused during his musical chores at the Savoy Ballroom Monday night to greet an admirer. The young lady's name is Doris [Dora] Noakes, who recently goes for the alto ace's type of music.  Carter spent several years in Europe before Adolf made things too hot for people over there.  He is one of the most versatile men of music, and is rated one-two with the best alto sax men in business.  His band is currently on a cross-country tour. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Saxophonist Benny Carter squatting on stage and shaking hands with Dora Noakes, surrounded by crowd, in Savoy Ballroom
